1
00:00:14,700 --> 00:00:17,967
Yen, we can stay home if you
don't feel comfortable going.

2
00:00:18,100 --> 00:00:20,567
But is it okay
if I give her a gift?

3
00:00:20,700 --> 00:00:21,733
I have a lot on my mind.

4
00:00:21,867 --> 00:00:23,800
That's why I thought
she had bad intentions.

5
00:00:23,933 --> 00:00:26,733
I want to show everyone
how beautiful you are.

6
00:00:26,867 --> 00:00:27,833
Okay, fine.

7
00:00:27,967 --> 00:00:29,733
We'll go to the party.

8
00:00:29,867 --> 00:00:32,267
You know what?
She doesn't deserve him.

9
00:00:32,400 --> 00:00:35,100
She's just making
Red's life miserable.

10
00:00:35,267 --> 00:00:38,767
Well, Yenyen has a
reason to feel insecure.

11
00:00:38,900 --> 00:00:41,200
Sabina, I knew it.

12
00:00:41,333 --> 00:00:42,667
You still haven't changed.

13
00:00:42,800 --> 00:00:45,200
Red had a blast the last
time we hung out together.

14
00:00:45,333 --> 00:00:46,933
When you'd lost your baby.

15
00:00:47,067 --> 00:00:48,367
I have proof.

16
00:00:48,500 --> 00:00:50,267
I'm happy now because
I'm a free man.

17
00:00:50,400 --> 00:00:53,300
You know, I don't have
to change diapers.

18
00:00:53,433 --> 00:00:55,033
Because my baby's gone.

19
00:00:55,167 --> 00:00:56,833
What else can I do?

20
00:00:56,967 --> 00:00:58,333
Looks like you're
having a lot of fun.

21
00:00:58,467 --> 00:00:59,667
Of course.

22
00:00:59,800 --> 00:01:01,767
This is the first time
we'll drink together.

23
00:01:01,900 --> 00:01:02,767
- Red!
- Why?
Because we don't
have a baby anymore?

24
00:01:03,867 --> 00:01:04,633
Let's take a shot at the bar.

25
00:01:04,767 --> 00:01:05,867
Shot? Come on.

26
00:01:06,000 --> 00:01:07,267
Yen, come on. Let's take a shot.

27
00:01:07,433 --> 00:01:10,633
God has given you
a lot of blessings.

28
00:01:10,767 --> 00:01:14,500
Maybe you can now reconcile
with the Ramoses.

29
00:01:14,633 --> 00:01:16,467
That will never happen.

30
00:01:16,600 --> 00:01:21,700
And I can't have them
in my and Eden's life forever.

31
00:01:21,833 --> 00:01:25,733
That's why I will show
Eden how evil they are.

32
00:01:25,867 --> 00:01:27,533
Have you seen Yenyen?

33
00:01:27,667 --> 00:01:29,233
Yenyen is not here.

34
00:01:29,367 --> 00:01:30,500
But I am.

35
00:01:30,633 --> 00:01:32,033
Wait!

36
00:01:32,167 --> 00:01:35,033
Red, you don't have to stay
with Yenyen out of pity.

37
00:01:35,167 --> 00:01:37,000
What Yenyen and I have is real.

38
00:01:37,133 --> 00:01:39,867
I know it. Because I yearned
for no one but her

39
00:01:40,000 --> 00:01:41,867
when we lost our baby.

40
00:01:42,033 --> 00:01:44,833
Who bought those
counterfeit money?

41
00:01:44,967 --> 00:01:46,233
Is it Amanda Madrigal?

42
00:01:46,367 --> 00:01:47,967
I don't know who she is!

43
00:01:48,100 --> 00:01:50,367
I'm just selling
my products.

44
00:01:50,500 --> 00:01:52,600
I don't know who bought it.

45
00:01:54,767 --> 00:01:58,467
I'm worried that someone else
might get hurt because of me.

46
00:01:58,600 --> 00:02:02,433
What if she also hurts
Eden just to get back at me?

47
00:02:02,567 --> 00:02:04,867
I want to get my
daughter back.

48
00:02:05,000 --> 00:02:07,233
Yen, I've been doing my
very best for both of us.

49
00:02:07,367 --> 00:02:08,600
I don't deserve this
treatment from you!

50
00:02:08,733 --> 00:02:09,933
Deserve?

51
00:02:10,067 --> 00:02:11,100
- What is going on with you?
- This is what you deserve!

52
00:02:11,233 --> 00:02:12,500
Get out! I'm tired already.

53
00:02:12,633 --> 00:02:13,367
Yen!

54
00:02:15,967 --> 00:02:17,100
Yen!

55
00:02:42,333 --> 00:02:44,967
I don't understand her, Mom.

56
00:02:45,100 --> 00:02:46,567
I thought we were okay now.

57
00:02:46,700 --> 00:02:53,033
But it's so easy for her
to accuse me.

58
00:02:53,200 --> 00:02:56,200
Women are really hard
to understand, Red.

59
00:03:00,567 --> 00:03:06,400
It could be connected
to her mother's return.

60
00:03:06,533 --> 00:03:09,533
Eden is confused again.

61
00:03:09,667 --> 00:03:14,167
And she's taking all her
frustrations out on you.

62
00:03:14,300 --> 00:03:16,000
I don't know, Mom.

63
00:03:16,133 --> 00:03:17,633
She seems different.

64
00:03:19,167 --> 00:03:24,567
She thinks I'm glad
that our child is gone.

65
00:03:24,733 --> 00:03:28,633
Didn't she know
I was miserable too?

66
00:03:31,033 --> 00:03:36,267
It's so hard because
I don't know how she feels.

67
00:03:41,100 --> 00:03:43,400
You know what
to do, right?

68
00:03:43,533 --> 00:03:44,567
Yes.

69
00:03:44,700 --> 00:03:46,733
I'll switch this
child with a dead one.

70
00:03:47,633 --> 00:03:50,600
I don't ever want to
see that child again.

71
00:03:50,733 --> 00:03:53,067
Thelma, make sure you
get that taken care of.

72
00:03:53,200 --> 00:03:54,400
I don't want any trouble.

73
00:03:54,567 --> 00:03:55,633
Don't worry.

74
00:03:55,767 --> 00:03:58,500
I know where I can sell
this child.

75
00:04:37,300 --> 00:04:40,767
I wish we didn't come back
to Manila.

76
00:04:44,167 --> 00:04:47,000
If only I knew
this would happen.

77
00:04:48,667 --> 00:04:51,767
I wish we'd just
stayed on the island.

78
00:05:30,067 --> 00:05:31,933
Okay, Mom.

79
00:05:32,067 --> 00:05:33,733
If you don't want anything
to do with me,

80
00:05:33,900 --> 00:05:37,733
then forget that I exist.

81
00:05:37,867 --> 00:05:41,733
Don't harm the people
who care for me.

82
00:05:44,167 --> 00:05:46,933
I'm sorry, Eden.

83
00:05:47,067 --> 00:05:49,633
Mom, when will
you move on?

84
00:05:51,567 --> 00:05:54,167
I've lost a lot already.

85
00:05:54,300 --> 00:05:56,667
You even harmed
my baby too.

86
00:05:58,600 --> 00:06:00,567
Mom, I lost my baby.

87
00:06:00,700 --> 00:06:02,200
I didn't even get to hug her.

88
00:06:02,333 --> 00:06:04,600
I didn't get to kiss her.

89
00:06:04,733 --> 00:06:07,567
I didn't even get
to hold her, Mom!

90
00:06:07,733 --> 00:06:08,633
Sorry.

91
00:06:08,767 --> 00:06:10,700
Sorry?

92
00:06:10,833 --> 00:06:14,300
It won't bring my baby back!

93
00:06:14,433 --> 00:06:17,667
Mom, I'm begging you,
please stop this.

94
00:06:17,800 --> 00:06:19,933
Let me go!

95
00:06:31,533 --> 00:06:32,400
Having a hard
time sleeping?

96
00:06:38,567 --> 00:06:40,800
I remember what Eden said.

97
00:06:45,967 --> 00:06:50,033
She said her child got involved
because of my hatred for Rina.

98
00:06:52,233 --> 00:06:54,033
What if she's right?

99
00:06:56,200 --> 00:06:59,467
I disowned Eden
because of Rina.

100
00:07:02,633 --> 00:07:07,133
What if I'm the
reason her baby died?

101
00:07:11,533 --> 00:07:13,300
Don't blame yourself.

102
00:07:15,367 --> 00:07:20,500
I'm not trying to
blame your daughter.

103
00:07:20,633 --> 00:07:22,833
But she wouldn't have lost
her child if she chose

104
00:07:22,967 --> 00:07:24,300
to be with you.

105
00:07:25,833 --> 00:07:30,033
If you were beside her, you were
the one who took care of her.

106
00:07:30,167 --> 00:07:34,500
She could have given
birth to her child safely.

107
00:07:39,833 --> 00:07:43,167
If she chose you,

108
00:07:43,300 --> 00:07:44,833
she would have had
a complete family.

109
00:08:41,867 --> 00:08:42,867
Yen.

110
00:08:45,500 --> 00:08:48,933
Yen, if you don't want to talk
to me, you should at least eat.

111
00:08:49,067 --> 00:08:50,700
Emma brought you breakfast.

112
00:08:51,967 --> 00:08:52,933
Yen.

113
00:09:04,300 --> 00:09:05,067
Yen?

114
00:09:18,667 --> 00:09:20,333
She's not here.

115
00:09:41,633 --> 00:09:45,700
Thank you for taking care of me.

116
00:09:45,833 --> 00:09:47,000
Goodbye.

117
00:09:58,700 --> 00:10:02,333
I'm sorry,
all circuits are busy.

118
00:10:04,300 --> 00:10:05,600
Her phone is off.

119
00:10:08,133 --> 00:10:10,833
Didn't you check on her before
you went to sleep last night?

120
00:10:12,367 --> 00:10:14,133
We had a big fight.

121
00:10:14,267 --> 00:10:15,933
That's why I didn't talk to her.

122
00:10:16,067 --> 00:10:18,300
I thought she needed more time.

123
00:10:18,433 --> 00:10:20,400
Look what happens when you don't
fix things right away.

124
00:10:20,533 --> 00:10:22,833
Eden left!

125
00:10:22,967 --> 00:10:25,467
Probably she went back
to Amanda already.

126
00:10:25,600 --> 00:10:27,700
My god, Red!

127
00:10:27,833 --> 00:10:30,267
After everything that
we have done for Eden.

128
00:10:30,400 --> 00:10:31,533
What?

129
00:10:31,667 --> 00:10:33,400
Only to go back to her mother?

130
00:10:33,533 --> 00:10:34,967
Hey.

131
00:10:35,133 --> 00:10:37,633
Red is worried about Eden.

132
00:10:37,767 --> 00:10:39,667
Stop talking about
your issue with Amanda.

133
00:10:39,800 --> 00:10:42,467
Everything is connected!

134
00:10:42,600 --> 00:10:45,033
I'm sure she's
with Amanda now.

135
00:10:45,167 --> 00:10:48,267
If you don't get Eden back,

136
00:10:48,400 --> 00:10:51,933
I'm sure Amanda will talk badly
about you to Eden.

137
00:10:52,067 --> 00:10:56,500
And then, the two of you will
never get back together again.

138
00:10:59,533 --> 00:11:01,433
I can't let that happen.

139
00:11:01,567 --> 00:11:04,733
I'll get Yenyen back
no matter what it takes!

140
00:11:07,000 --> 00:11:08,133
Red?

141
00:11:08,300 --> 00:11:08,900
Red.

142
00:11:09,033 --> 00:11:10,333
Red, wait!

143
00:11:10,467 --> 00:11:11,467
Son!

144
00:11:11,600 --> 00:11:13,700
We should follow him.

145
00:11:13,833 --> 00:11:16,033
He can't go there by himself!

146
00:11:19,233 --> 00:11:19,900
Yen!

147
00:11:21,133 --> 00:11:21,967
Yenyen!

148
00:11:22,100 --> 00:11:23,033
I'm here now, Yen!

149
00:11:24,233 --> 00:11:25,667
- Don't touch my son!
- Yen!

150
00:11:25,800 --> 00:11:26,967
What's going on?

151
00:11:27,100 --> 00:11:27,867
Yenyen!

152
00:11:29,133 --> 00:11:30,400
- Red?
- Ma'am, I'm sorry.

153
00:11:30,533 --> 00:11:32,067
Yenyen, where are you?

154
00:11:32,200 --> 00:11:33,900
What are you doing here?

155
00:11:35,733 --> 00:11:36,767
I'm sorry, Ma'am.

156
00:11:36,900 --> 00:11:38,233
I couldn't stop them
from barging in.

157
00:11:38,367 --> 00:11:39,367
What's going on?

158
00:11:39,500 --> 00:11:40,867
Yenyen!

159
00:11:41,900 --> 00:11:43,333
Ma'am, Sir, I'm sorry.

160
00:11:43,467 --> 00:11:46,233
I tried to stop them but
they forced their way in.

161
00:11:46,367 --> 00:11:48,267
I thought you guys were wealthy.

162
00:11:48,400 --> 00:11:51,167
Why can't you buy good manners?

163
00:11:51,300 --> 00:11:56,600
Did you know that coming over
without notice is bad etiquette?

164
00:11:56,733 --> 00:11:58,400
We're not here to visit you.

165
00:11:58,533 --> 00:12:00,133
We're here to get Yenyen.

166
00:12:00,267 --> 00:12:01,133
Where is she?

167
00:12:02,400 --> 00:12:03,467
- Yen!
- She's staying with you,

168
00:12:03,600 --> 00:12:04,633
isn't she?

169
00:12:04,767 --> 00:12:06,967
Why are you looking
for her here?

170
00:12:08,733 --> 00:12:11,000
Is she not here?

171
00:12:11,133 --> 00:12:12,967
She's not here.
What are you talking about?

172
00:12:15,267 --> 00:12:17,233
Is Eden missing?

173
00:12:23,133 --> 00:12:24,400
What did you do to my daughter?

174
00:12:25,733 --> 00:12:26,900
Why did she leave?

175
00:12:27,033 --> 00:12:28,433
Excuse me!

176
00:12:28,567 --> 00:12:30,867
Don't you dare blame my son!

177
00:12:31,000 --> 00:12:34,800
You don't know anything because
you abandoned your daughter!

178
00:12:34,933 --> 00:12:35,733
Oh, please!

179
00:12:35,867 --> 00:12:37,000
Shut up!

180
00:12:39,433 --> 00:12:41,600
Don't try to tell me you're
treating my daughter

181
00:12:41,733 --> 00:12:42,900
as your own!

182
00:12:43,033 --> 00:12:45,733
She ran away from
you, didn't she?

183
00:12:48,000 --> 00:12:49,833
I knew it!

184
00:12:50,000 --> 00:12:53,967
Yenyen is not happy
with you guys!

185
00:12:54,100 --> 00:12:57,533
Once I get proof that you're
mistreating my daughter,

186
00:12:57,667 --> 00:13:00,067
I will make you pay!

187
00:13:00,200 --> 00:13:02,767
We're not mistreating her.

188
00:13:02,900 --> 00:13:05,000
We're taking good care of her.

189
00:13:05,133 --> 00:13:07,000
We just had a misunderstanding.

190
00:13:07,133 --> 00:13:07,967
That's it.

191
00:13:08,100 --> 00:13:09,533
Why did she leave
without telling you

192
00:13:09,667 --> 00:13:12,000
if it was just
a misunderstanding?

193
00:13:12,133 --> 00:13:13,667
I'm sorry.

194
00:13:13,800 --> 00:13:15,467
I apologize, Lucho.

195
00:13:15,600 --> 00:13:18,533
We just didn't expect
that Yenyen would run away.

196
00:13:20,300 --> 00:13:22,433
You'll have to explain
to Amanda about that.

197
00:13:22,600 --> 00:13:23,900
No, wait a minute.

198
00:13:24,033 --> 00:13:25,367
Why are you saying sorry?

199
00:13:25,500 --> 00:13:27,433
We didn't do anything wrong.

200
00:13:28,467 --> 00:13:30,800
We've given Eden a home.

201
00:13:30,933 --> 00:13:33,800
And now she's blaming us!

202
00:13:33,933 --> 00:13:35,033
Wait a minute.

203
00:13:35,167 --> 00:13:38,000
No wonder your daughter doesn't
want to come home to you.

204
00:13:38,133 --> 00:13:39,000
See?

205
00:13:39,133 --> 00:13:40,767
She has nowhere else to go,

206
00:13:40,900 --> 00:13:43,633
but she chose not
to come back to you!

207
00:13:43,767 --> 00:13:45,200
Impertinent!

208
00:13:45,333 --> 00:13:48,500
Remember this,
especially you, Red.

209
00:13:48,633 --> 00:13:51,867
If I get to Eden before you do,

210
00:13:52,000 --> 00:13:54,633
I will make sure she won't
be coming back to you!

211
00:13:54,800 --> 00:13:57,000
And your relationship
will be over!

212
00:13:57,133 --> 00:13:59,067
Do you understand?

213
00:13:59,200 --> 00:14:00,633
Get out of here!

214
00:14:03,733 --> 00:14:04,400
- Let's go.
- Red. Red.

215
00:14:04,533 --> 00:14:06,200
- Let's go, Red.
- Red, come on.

216
00:14:22,200 --> 00:14:23,100
Raichu.

217
00:14:24,133 --> 00:14:24,900
Raichu.

218
00:14:25,033 --> 00:14:26,267
Raichu, please, wait!

219
00:14:27,700 --> 00:14:29,433
You are Yenyen's best friend.

220
00:14:29,600 --> 00:14:32,000
I'm sure you know where she is.

221
00:14:32,133 --> 00:14:33,767
Is she staying with you?

222
00:14:33,900 --> 00:14:35,367
I'm staying in a dormitory.

223
00:14:35,500 --> 00:14:37,600
I can't keep a visitor
overnight.

224
00:14:37,733 --> 00:14:41,000
I know! But I know that you know
where she is.

225
00:14:41,133 --> 00:14:43,000
Look, okay, we have problems.

226
00:14:43,133 --> 00:14:44,767
I still don't know what to do.

227
00:14:44,900 --> 00:14:46,533
But I'm willing to look
for solutions.

228
00:14:46,667 --> 00:14:48,833
As long as we don't
give up on each other.

229
00:14:48,967 --> 00:14:53,400
Raichu, don't you see how much
I love your best friend?

230
00:14:53,533 --> 00:14:54,433
I can see it.

231
00:14:55,833 --> 00:14:58,933
But I can't do anything
to help you.

232
00:14:59,067 --> 00:15:00,300
I don't know where she is.

233
00:15:00,433 --> 00:15:02,467
I don't know what she's
planning to do, okay?

234
00:15:03,767 --> 00:15:04,800
I have a shift today.

235
00:15:04,933 --> 00:15:06,500
Can I go to work now?

236
00:15:13,033 --> 00:15:13,900
Hey, bro.

237
00:15:14,033 --> 00:15:16,600
Bro, you need to
know something.

238
00:15:57,200 --> 00:15:58,200
Oh my god!

239
00:16:00,100 --> 00:16:01,433
Aunt Amanda?

240
00:16:01,567 --> 00:16:03,333
Is that you?

241
00:16:03,467 --> 00:16:05,933
Raichu, where is Eden?

242
00:16:06,067 --> 00:16:07,533
Auntie...

243
00:16:11,000 --> 00:16:13,567
I'm sure she talked to you.

244
00:16:13,700 --> 00:16:15,167
I know that you know
where she is.

245
00:16:24,900 --> 00:16:26,100
Raichu, you scared
the heck out of me.

246
00:16:26,233 --> 00:16:27,633
I thought you
were someone else.

247
00:16:27,767 --> 00:16:30,167
Sorry, Eden.
I had to borrow this car first.

248
00:16:30,300 --> 00:16:31,300
Oh, stop it.

249
00:16:31,433 --> 00:16:33,767
I should apologize
instead for bothering you.

250
00:16:33,900 --> 00:16:34,967
You're unbelievable.

251
00:16:35,100 --> 00:16:37,567
Why did you run away
all of a sudden?

252
00:16:37,700 --> 00:16:38,967
Are you sure about this?

253
00:16:39,100 --> 00:16:41,367
Can't you work
things out with Red?

254
00:16:41,500 --> 00:16:42,267
I don't want to.

255
00:16:42,433 --> 00:16:46,000
You're so stubborn.

256
00:16:46,133 --> 00:16:48,900
If I were you,
I would go back to my mom.

257
00:16:49,033 --> 00:16:50,467
You know where she lives, right?

258
00:16:50,600 --> 00:16:52,333
I'll drop you off. Let's go.

259
00:16:52,467 --> 00:16:54,867
Raichu, I don't want
to see my mom or Red.

260
00:16:55,000 --> 00:16:56,367
I have another plan.

261
00:16:58,467 --> 00:17:04,267
No matter what happens,
don't tell anyone where I am.

262
00:17:04,400 --> 00:17:05,133
Okay?

263
00:17:11,200 --> 00:17:14,167
I have a right to know.
I'm still her mom!

264
00:17:19,367 --> 00:17:22,700
Bro, I'm sorry I didn't
get to tell you sooner.

265
00:17:23,667 --> 00:17:26,033
Sab has been telling me
that she's still not over you.

266
00:17:26,167 --> 00:17:28,367
And she'll make you realize,

267
00:17:28,500 --> 00:17:30,267
that you and Eden are not
meant for each other.

268
00:17:31,800 --> 00:17:34,333
But I didn't know
she would do something

269
00:17:34,467 --> 00:17:36,733
against the two of you.

270
00:17:38,033 --> 00:17:39,700
What do you mean?

271
00:17:39,833 --> 00:17:43,167
Sab was so upset
when you left her party.

272
00:17:43,300 --> 00:17:45,700
She was so drunk.

273
00:17:45,833 --> 00:17:49,200
And she kept telling me
that no matter what you do,

274
00:17:49,367 --> 00:17:52,267
Eden won't get over that video.

275
00:17:52,400 --> 00:17:53,700
What video?

276
00:17:54,900 --> 00:17:57,167
I got curious about the video
she kept telling me about.

277
00:17:58,600 --> 00:18:00,933
That's why I
took her phone.

278
00:18:01,067 --> 00:18:03,033
And this is what I saw.

279
00:18:04,633 --> 00:18:08,333
I'm happy now because
I'm a free man, you know.

280
00:18:08,467 --> 00:18:10,800
No changing diapers for me.

281
00:18:10,933 --> 00:18:13,900
No baby bottles.

282
00:18:14,033 --> 00:18:15,667
Because my baby's gone.

283
00:18:15,800 --> 00:18:17,733
What else can I do, right?

284
00:18:19,367 --> 00:18:21,133
So let's just have fun!

285
00:18:21,300 --> 00:18:22,767
This is the life!

286
00:18:22,900 --> 00:18:25,000
So I said this.

287
00:18:25,133 --> 00:18:27,467
But that's not the whole video.

288
00:18:27,600 --> 00:18:28,600
I don't know
if you still remember,

289
00:18:28,733 --> 00:18:30,700
but you were crying after that.

290
00:18:30,833 --> 00:18:33,567
You were in so much pain
from losing your baby.

291
00:18:34,567 --> 00:18:37,667
But Sab edited the video
and cut off that part.

292
00:18:37,800 --> 00:18:40,967
And I'm sure that's
what she showed Eden.

293
00:18:44,700 --> 00:18:49,600
Now I understand why Eden
was so angry with me.

294
00:18:51,833 --> 00:18:53,100
Don't worry, bro.

295
00:18:53,233 --> 00:18:55,833
I got a copy of the full video.

296
00:18:56,000 --> 00:18:57,733
I'll send it to you.

297
00:18:57,867 --> 00:19:00,700
I hope this can help you
fix things with Eden.

298
00:19:03,433 --> 00:19:04,867
Thank you.

299
00:20:37,333 --> 00:20:39,067
Are you sure you want
to stay here by yourself?

300
00:20:39,200 --> 00:20:40,800
This place is dangerous
when there's a typhoon coming.

301
00:20:43,433 --> 00:20:47,733
I survived all the trials
on this island before.

302
00:20:47,867 --> 00:20:49,500
I can do it again.

303
00:20:51,100 --> 00:20:53,533
I just need time to be alone.

304
00:20:55,100 --> 00:20:56,567
Okay then, be safe.

305
00:20:56,700 --> 00:20:57,733
I'll get going now.

306
00:20:57,867 --> 00:20:59,433
Thank you, Sir.

307
00:22:07,867 --> 00:22:09,767
I thought you had a lot
of connections.

308
00:22:11,333 --> 00:22:13,900
You can't even find Eden.

309
00:22:14,033 --> 00:22:15,500
I don't know where she is.

310
00:22:15,667 --> 00:22:17,433
She's nowhere to be seen.

311
00:22:18,933 --> 00:22:22,167
At least she didn't
go back to Amanda.

312
00:22:22,300 --> 00:22:24,167
So we can still do something

313
00:22:24,300 --> 00:22:27,800
as long as they're not yet
reunited.

314
00:22:27,933 --> 00:22:30,700
Rina, do you really
want Eden back?

315
00:22:30,833 --> 00:22:32,567
Isn't it a hassle?

316
00:22:32,700 --> 00:22:36,467
If it's up to me, I don't
care if she disappears!

317
00:22:36,600 --> 00:22:37,633
She's so fuzzy.

318
00:22:37,767 --> 00:22:42,133
She's full of drama,
just like her mother.

319
00:22:42,267 --> 00:22:45,333
She does nothing but
causes us trouble.

320
00:22:47,500 --> 00:22:51,633
Fortunately,
we got rid of the baby.

321
00:22:51,800 --> 00:22:52,967
Mom.

322
00:22:55,200 --> 00:22:57,633
Are you talking about my baby?

323
00:23:04,533 --> 00:23:05,833
I called Zandro.

324
00:23:05,967 --> 00:23:08,533
I asked him to
help us find Red.

325
00:23:08,667 --> 00:23:11,900
If something bad happens to my
son while looking for Eden,

326
00:23:12,033 --> 00:23:13,233
I'll make her pay!

327
00:23:13,367 --> 00:23:17,467
How she wishes that she
had gone back to her mom!

328
00:23:17,600 --> 00:23:22,333
This is the place where
Rina and Zandro tortured me.

329
00:23:22,500 --> 00:23:25,033
I'm sure this is where they
bring in people

330
00:23:25,167 --> 00:23:26,267
who mess with them.

331
00:23:26,400 --> 00:23:27,867
This place is hidden.

332
00:23:28,000 --> 00:23:29,267
That's why they
don't need security.

333
00:23:29,400 --> 00:23:30,933
It will make our job easier.

334
00:23:31,067 --> 00:23:32,467
Stop worrying about your son.

335
00:23:32,600 --> 00:23:33,700
He's old enough.

336
00:23:33,833 --> 00:23:36,000
You should think about what's
about to happen tonight.

337
00:23:36,133 --> 00:23:37,567
Because I know where
to find the man

338
00:23:37,700 --> 00:23:38,933
that cheated us of our money.

339
00:23:39,067 --> 00:23:42,767
Now I can get my
revenge on that monster.

340
00:23:44,800 --> 00:23:46,933
Are you ready to confess now?

341
00:23:47,067 --> 00:23:47,733
Tell me the truth!
No!

342
00:23:51,667 --> 00:23:53,267
Let him go!

343
00:23:53,400 --> 00:23:54,133
Put your gun down!

344
00:23:55,467 --> 00:23:56,667
Zandro!

345
00:23:58,900 --> 00:24:00,800
Take off your mask.

346
00:24:00,933 --> 00:24:03,967
I know that it's you, Rina.

347
00:24:04,100 --> 00:24:05,900
I just want to see your face.
